HEADWORD: Dermopteran
<hw>Der*mop"ter*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An insect which has the anterior pair of wings coriaceous, and does
not use them in flight, as the earwig.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

